The paper deals with building successful recommender systems that require modeling the visual appearance of items, which falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also addresses the challenges of sparsity and variability in real-world datasets, which is a common problem in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper proposes a novel hierarchical embedding architecture, which involves modeling the visual characteristics of different product categories, making it relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL) and multimedia (cs.MM).
